General.Name: Nexus Infrastructure plc
General.Description: Nexus Infrastructure plc offers infrastructure and civil engineering services to the housebuilding and commercial sectors in the United Kingdom. It operates through three segments: Tamdown, TriConnex, and eSmart Networks. The company undertakes earthworks; builds highways, substructures, and basements; and installs drainage systems. It also designs, installs, and connects gas, electricity, water, and fiber networks for residential developments; provides public electric vehicle charging infrastructure, industrial electrification, and connections to renewable energy sources. The company was formerly known as Garbol plc and changed its name to Nexus Infrastructure plc in June 2016. Nexus Infrastructure plc was founded in 1976 and is headquartered in Braintree, the United Kingdom.
